{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"795b6292-899f-43d1-822d-8e0cc35d6b7d","agentId":"a4053cef465153bd0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Cleanup finder, angles: REUSE + SIMPLIFICATION. Repo: c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test. Scope = full uncommitted change-set vs HEAD (usage-export feature). REUSE: new code re-implementing existing helpers — does usage_export duplicate usage.py's window-bound validation instead of importing it? does the route re-declare the auth+throttle dependency instead of reusing the sibling pattern appropriately? do the new tests re-implement conftest fixtures? SIMPLIFICATION: dead code from the optimization pass (leftover per-row helpers, the old escape loop, unused imports, the superseded _is_safe_character), redundant state, copy-paste between the 5 new test files, derivable constants duplicated (100k cap defined in more than one place?), YAGNI/dead-flexibility knobs (env vars or params nothing legitimately varies — the R2-9/R2-10 class). Name the existing helper / simpler form; failure_scenario = concrete cost.\nReturn up to 6 candidates: file, line, summary, cost. If none, say none."},"uuid":"3d01cc00-6fcf-4c9c-be58-0b0284ae1bbd","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:47:45.395Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
